# GCS Storage Module

This Terraform module creates a Google Cloud Storage bucket optimized for storing parquet files with partitions. It includes lifecycle management, IAM bindings, encryption, and security best practices.

## Features

- **Lifecycle Management**: Automatic storage class transitions (STANDARD → NEARLINE → COLDLINE → ARCHIVE)
- **Data Retention**: Configurable retention periods with automatic deletion
- **IAM Integration**: Support for readers, writers, and admins
- **Encryption**: Support for Google-managed or customer-managed KMS keys
- **Security**: Public access prevention enforced, uniform bucket-level access
- **Logging**: Optional access logging for production environments
- **CORS**: Optional CORS configuration for web-based access

## Usage

### Basic Example

```hcl
module "gcs_parquet_storage" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Gcp/GCS"

  project_id  = "my-project-id"
  bucket_name = "my-project-parquet-data"

  # Basic configuration
  location      = "US-CENTRAL1"
  storage_class = "STANDARD"

  # Lifecycle management
  nearline_transition_days = 30
  coldline_transition_days = 90
  archive_transition_days  = 365
  data_retention_days      = 180

  # IAM members
  data_readers = [
    "serviceAccount:reader@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]
  data_writers = [
    "serviceAccount:writer@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]
}
```

### Production Example with Encryption and Logging

```hcl
module "gcs_parquet_storage" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Gcp/GCS"

  project_id  = "my-project-id"
  bucket_name = "my-project-parquet-data-prod"

  # Multi-region for high availability
  location      = "US"
  storage_class = "STANDARD"

  # Lifecycle management
  nearline_transition_days = 30
  coldline_transition_days = 90
  archive_transition_days  = 365
  data_retention_days      = 2555  # 7 years

  # Retention policy
  retention_period_seconds = 2592000  # 30 days
  lock_retention_policy    = false

  # Customer-managed encryption
  kms_key_name = "projects/my-project/locations/us-central1/keyRings/data-keyring/cryptoKeys/parquet-key"

  # Access logging
  log_bucket_name = "my-project-access-logs"
  log_object_prefix = "parquet-storage-logs"

  # IAM members
  data_readers = [
    "serviceAccount:analytics@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]
  data_writers = [
    "serviceAccount:pipeline@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]
  data_admins = [
    "serviceAccount:admin@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]

  # Labels
  labels = {
    environment = "production"
    team        = "data-engineering"
  }
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|----------|
| `project_id` | The GCP project ID where the bucket will be created | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `bucket_name` | The globally unique name for the GCS bucket | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `location` | The location (region or multi-region) for the bucket | `string` | `"US-CENTRAL1"` | no |
| `storage_class` | The default storage class for the bucket | `string` | `"STANDARD"` | no |
| `enable_versioning` | Whether to enable versioning | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `nearline_transition_days` | Days before transitioning to NEARLINE | `number` | `30` | no |
| `coldline_transition_days` | Days before transitioning to COLDLINE | `number` | `90` | no |
| `archive_transition_days` | Days before transitioning to ARCHIVE | `number` | `365` | no |
| `data_retention_days` | Days to retain data before deletion | `number` | `180` | no |
| `retention_period_seconds` | Minimum retention period in seconds (0 to disable) | `number` | `0` | no |
| `lock_retention_policy` | Whether to lock the retention policy | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `kms_key_name` | KMS key name for encryption (null for Google-managed) | `string` | `null` | no |
| `log_bucket_name` | Bucket name for access logs (null to disable) | `string` | `null` | no |
| `log_object_prefix` | Object prefix for log objects | `string` | `"parquet-storage-logs"` | no |
| `cors_config` | CORS configuration object (null to disable) | `object` | `null` | no |
| `data_readers` | List of IAM members with read access | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `data_writers` | List of IAM members with write access | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `data_admins` | List of IAM members with admin access | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `labels` | Additional labels for the bucket | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `bucket_name` | The name of the GCS bucket |
| `bucket_url` | The URL of the GCS bucket |
| `bucket_self_link` | The self link of the GCS bucket |
| `bucket_location` | The location of the GCS bucket |
| `bucket_storage_class` | The default storage class of the GCS bucket |
| `parquet_storage_path` | The gs:// path for the parquet storage bucket |
| `bucket_id` | The ID of the GCS bucket |

## Lifecycle Management

The module automatically manages storage costs by transitioning data through storage classes:

1. **STANDARD** (days 0-30): Frequently accessed data
2. **NEARLINE** (days 30-90): Infrequently accessed data
3. **COLDLINE** (days 90-365): Rarely accessed data
4. **ARCHIVE** (days 365+): Long-term archival storage
5. **DELETE** (after retention period): Automatic cleanup


## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| google | >= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0 |

## Notes

- Bucket names must be globally unique
- Lifecycle rules apply automatically to all objects in the bucket
- Retention policies cannot be reduced once locked
- CORS configuration is optional and only needed for web-based access
